    /// The [`LeafSpan`] for an absorbed-anonymous SEQ MEMBER at the cursor:
    /// the enclosing `node` plus the byte range between the previous
    /// child's end (or the node's start, if the cursor is at the first
    /// child) and the next child's start (or the node's end, if no child
    /// remains). tree-sitter absorbs such a token with NO child of its own,
    /// so this reads the inter-sibling text WITHOUT advancing the cursor
    /// (nothing is consumed; the adjacent siblings are placed by their own
    /// positions). `checked_sub` / `get` keep it panic- and
